  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">RECOVER</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">RECOVER aims to build livelihood resilience to recurrent shocks (drought and flood) in vulnerable populations by strengthening and diversifying livelihoods patterns. Specific endemic and persistent shocks include ongoing drought conditions in the Somali Region, particularly in Gode and Warder Zones, and the devastating impact of seasonal flooding affecting vulnerable communities in Gode Zone.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The activities focus on early recovery in order to diversify livelihoods, increase household risk resilience and increase and improve water supply for vulnerable pastoral dropout and agro-pastoral communities.</narrative>
  </description>
